<Author>NAURU
<Content>Casa Inn - Noisy and Expensive A friend recommended this hotel because of the area it is in (close to the Zona Rosa). However, I was extremely disappointed with it - most of all because of the noise.  The noise comes from the street called Rio Mississippi which it is on. This is a major traffic route, packed with cars all night long, and the people of Mexico City constantly blow their horns. As a result, I couldn't sleep at all. I also found the night-time front-desk staff to be surly.  The only plus was the buffet breakfast, which was excellent. But who cares, if you can't sleep at night ? I paid $80 a night not to sleep !  I then transferred to the New York Hotel, which was only $32, and very quiet, with friendly staff. 
