<Author>pedirto
<Content>the worst of our stay Our first hotel in DF was in the NH Centro Historico, which obviously was a very nice hotel. After coming back to DF from San Miguel de Allende, we decided to stay at Casa Inn. The room needed cleaning, the walls were kind of dirty, the carpet dirty too, and a few of the bathroom's tiles were broken. The overall quality of the room was very low.Since I had to leave at 6am, the lady in charge of the breakfast told me that I would get a bag with some cakes before departing as my breakfast was included with my room. The morning that I had to leave I went down to the front desk at 5:30am but the person there told me that he had not been informed about providing any breakfast for my room. I just could not believe that I had paid for my breakfast and the manager just let me go without it. I told them to call me a cab to go to the airport and they got me a private SUV. I told the driver that I just needed a regular cab, which usually charges you around $35 from that area to the airport (I had done it before). He said that a regular taxi would charge me around $180. Since I had to rush to take my flight, I had to pay him $150 for the ride. I was ripped off, and the hotel was responsible for getting me this kind of transportation. Pick another hotel if you can, they are irresponsible and incompetent. 
