<Content>Friendly but slow service Cassa Inn.. the room was nice..nice big tv,however, no one informed us that there was a need fora deposit for a remote...went down, gave thedeposit..the control didn't work. Called the frontdesk and was told that someone would bring oneshortly...no one came. Next day, someone came withthe wrong control. Turns out they didn't have anycontrols for that TV brand. Was told they wouldchange our TV, than told they couldn't do that. Sopaid a deposit for no remote control. Room serviceworst than that. When it didn't take an hour to getour food, they gave it to another room.There was no kettle or coffee maker in the room...sohad to go without it. Their carpets need cleaning. Towards the end of our stay we decided againstcomplaining anymore since they were so slow torespond.However, no complains about the location. We lovedthat we could walk to the Zona Rosa. The area is very nice overall. 
